## redteam adversarial plan review (codex · agent-pair)
Reviewed `input.md`, `outcome.md`, `state.json`, and `.redteam/prompts/codex/plan_review.md` for task `task-033-fit-synonyms`.

---

PR-001 severity:blocker status:open

`outcome.md` does not include the required parseable `## Verification` fenced `yaml` block with at least one command. The plan-review criteria explicitly blocks when `outcome.md` lacks this structure. The current file has `## Verification hooks` with Markdown bullets, but no fenced YAML block such as:

```yaml
commands:
  - bash .redteam/scripts/verify.sh
```

This must be added under an exact `## Verification` heading before implementation proceeds.

New-test justification: The planned tests are appropriate and would fail against pre-change code because aliases like `k8s`/`kubernetes`, `postgres`/`postgresql`, and `js`/`javascript` currently do not canonicalize to the same token set.

Verification note: This was a plan review only. No verification commands were run, and no files were modified.

REVIEW_DECISION: CHANGES_REQUESTED
